  "prompt": "Why is the climbing equipment ATC named what it is?",
  "response": "ATC stands for \"Air Traffic Controller,\" which might seem odd for a piece of climbing equipment. The term originated from the Black Diamond ATC (Air Traffic Controller) belay device, which was designed by Grenville Pullen, a product manager at Black Diamond, in the 1990s. The device's shape and function reminded him of an air traffic controller directing traffic, hence the name. Despite the seemingly unrelated origin, the name stuck and is now commonly used to refer to similar belay devices, even from other manufacturers.",
